          }
        ],
        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The probability mass function (PMF) for the binomial distribution is"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "P(N) = \\binom{n}{N}p^N(1-p)^{n-N},"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the number of trials, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "p"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the probability\nof success, and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "N"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the number of successes."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "When estimating the standard error of a proportion in a population by\nusing a random sample, the normal distribution works well unless the\nproduct p*n <=5, where p = population proportion estimate, and n =\nnumber of samples, in which case the binomial distribution is used\ninstead. For example, a sample of 15 people shows 4 who are left\nhanded, and 11 who are right handed. Then p = 4/15 = 27%. 0.27*15 = 4,\nso the binomial distribution should be used in this case."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nDalgaard, Peter, \"Introductory Statistics with R\",\nSpringer-Verlag, 2002.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nGlantz, Stanton A. \"Primer of Biostatistics.\", McGraw-Hill,\nFifth Edition, 2002.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "3\n\nLentner, Marvin, \"Elementary Applied Statistics\", Bogden\nand Quigley, 1972.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "4\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Binomial Distribution.\" From MathWorld--A\nWolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/BinomialDistribution.html",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "5\n\nWikipedia, \"Binomial distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_distribution",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "rng = flops.random.default_rng()"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "n, p, size = 10, .5, 10000"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = rng.binomial(n, p, 10000)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Assume a company drills 9 wild-cat oil exploration wells, each with\nan estimated probability of success of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "p=0.1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ". All nine wells fail.\nWhat is the probability of that happening?"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Over "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "size = 20,000"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " trials the probability of this happening\nis on average:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "n, p, size = 9, 0.1, 20000"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "flops.sum(rng.binomial(n=n, p=p, size=size) == 0)/size"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "0.39015  # may vary"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The following can be used to visualize a sample with "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "n=100"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ",\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "p=0.4"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and the corresponding probability density function:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "from scipy.stats import binom"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "n, p, size = 100, 0.4, 10000"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "sample = rng.binomial(n, p, size=size)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "count, bins, _ = plt.hist(sample, 30, density=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = flops.arange(n)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "y = binom.pmf(x, n, p)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(x, y, linewidth=2, color='r')"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
    ]
  },
